Installation

To use secure_deploy_ops.py, you must have Python 3 installed on your system.

    Clone the repository to your local machine using git clone https://github.com/<username>/<repository-name>.git.
    Navigate to the repository directory using cd <repository-name>.
    Install the required Python packages using pip install -r requirements.txt.
    Set the required environment variables for your infrastructure provider (e.g. AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID and AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY for AWS).

Usage

secure_deploy_ops.py can be run from the command line using the following command:

python secure_deploy_ops.py

When you run the script, it will:

    Deploy the infrastructure using Terraform or CloudFormation (placeholder code included in the script).
    Perform security checks to verify that the infrastructure is secure.
    Run tests using pytest or unittest (placeholder code included in the script).
